text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia quinquenervia is a shrub of the genus Acacia and the subgenus Phyllodineae. It is native to an area in the Wheatbelt and Goldfields-Esperance regions of Western Australia.The shrub typically grows to a height of 0.2 to 1.5 metres (0.7 to 4.9 ft) and produces yellow flowers.
